  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.",
    "Add the lamb cubes and brown them on all sides.",
    "Stir in the sliced challots and red bell pepper and cook until softened.",
    "Sprinkle in cumin, smoked paprika, oregano, chili powder, salt, and black pepper, and stir to coat the meat and vegetables.",
    "Pour in the water and bring the mixture to a boil.",
    "Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 60 minutes until the lamb is tender.",
    "Add the cooked white rice to the pot and stir to combine.",
    "Simmer for an additional 10 minutes to allow the flavors to meld.",
    "Taste and adjust seasoning if needed.",
    "Serve hot, spooning some stew over each plate."
